<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-21T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00 Elections/74: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-21T11:00:00-05:00">April 21, 1930—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>73. This morning the Council of State sitting as National Assembly
                            unanimously elected Eugene Roy President of Haiti. Twenty-one votes
                            cast. I shall immediately recognize Mr. Roy as the Presidentelect.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>